  "title": "Work Done in Stretching a Wire",
  "concepts": [
    {
      "title": "Elastic Energy",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Elastic Energy&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>When an elastic body is deformed, work is done by the applied force. This work is stored as elastic potential energy and is released when the body returns back to its original shape or size.</p><p>We have already come across an example of elastic potential energy in case of a compressed or stretched spring. The general expression for the elastic potential energy is a unit volume of a deformed body is given by:</p><p>Elastic energy stored per unit volume $=1/2$ (stress) (strain)</p><p>$=1/2~\\left( \\text{modulus }\\text{ of }\\text{ elasticity) }{{(\\text{ strain })}^{2}} \\right.$</p><p>In the case of a longitudinal stress (compressive or tensile)</p><p>$\\frac{\\text{ Energy }\\text{ stored }}{\\text{ volume }}=\\frac{1}{2}\\text{Y}{{\\left( \\frac{\\Delta\\text{ l}}{\\text{l}} \\right)}^{2}}$</p><p>Total energy $=\\frac{1}{2}\\frac{\\text{YA}}{\\text{l}}\\cdot {{(\\Delta\\text{ l})}^{2}}$</p><p>Total energy $=\\frac{1}{2}\\text{ F }\\Delta\\text{ l}$</p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db84c03b9dcaf1afe227"
    },
    {
      "title": "Torsion",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Torsion</strong>&nbsp;</h3><p>Consider a cylinder whose upper end is rigidity fixed and the other end is twisted through an angle $\\theta $ about the axis of the cylinder. The twisted cylinder exerts a restoring torque given by:</p><p>$\\tau =\\frac{1}{2}\\frac{\\pi \\eta {{r}^{4}}}{1}\\theta $</p><p>where $\\text{n}$ is the modulus of rigidity, $\\text{r}$ is the radius and $\\text{l}$ is the length of the cylinder.</p><figure class=\"image\"><img style=\"aspect-ratio:186/160;\" src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"186\" height=\"160\"></figure><p>If we express torque as $\\tau =\\text{C}\\theta $,</p><p>then $\\text{C}=\\frac{\\pi \\eta {{\\text{r}}^{4}}}{21}\\theta $ is known as the torsional rigidity.</p>",
      "position": 1,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db84c03b9dcaf1afe228"
    }
  ],
